uzix.UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller\/init(stringToScroll:duration:font:alignment:xOffset:width:height:)","title":"init(stringToScroll:duration:font:alignment:xOffset:width:height:)","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller\/init(stringtoscroll:duration:font:alignment:xoffset:width:height:)"},"doc://com.vuzix.UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/AutoScroller":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"AutoScroller is a utility class to send a large known block of predfined text to the glasses to be smoothly scrolled."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This is simlar to what is seen on a teleprompter or in movie credits.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This class was written using the "},{"code":"ScrollLayout","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" commands and is nothing more than a convience class."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Everything used this class can be written from the public SDK."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It scrolls the text much like a teleprompter would with basic commands to pause and resume the scrolling."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The duration (speed) of the scrolling can be modified while scrolling by seting the ","type":"text"},{"code":"duration","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" property."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It can support any language that the font supports."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"If the content is not known up front, or subject to change, this is the utility class will not work (use ","type":"text"},{"code":"LiveText","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance instead)."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vuzix.UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller","title":"ScrollLayout.AutoScroller","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AutoScroller","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/